00:16:07,820 --> 00:16:09,820
So that's a good thing.

282
00:16:09,820 --> 00:16:11,820
And the second thing is

283
00:16:11,820 --> 00:16:13,820
it's about actually being in control,

284
00:16:13,820 --> 00:16:15,820
but in a very special way.

285
00:16:15,820 --> 00:16:18,820
When Kleiber does -- did you see the eyes,

286
00:16:18,820 --> 00:16:20,820
going from here? (Singing)

287
00:16:20,820 --> 00:16:24,820
You know what happens? Gravitation is no more.

288
00:16:24,820 --> 00:16:26,820
Kleiber not only creates a process,

289
00:16:26,820 --> 00:16:29,820
but also creates the conditions in the world

290
00:16:29,820 --> 00:16:32,820
in which this process takes place.

291
00:16:32,820 --> 00:16:34,820
So again, the oboe player

292
00:16:34,820 --> 00:16:36,820
is completely autonomous

293
00:16:36,820 --> 00:16:39,820
and therefore happy and proud of his work,

294
00:16:39,820 --> 00:16:41,820
and creative and all of that.

295
00:16:41,820 --> 00:16:45,820
And the level in which Kleiber is in control is in a different level.

296
00:16:45,820 --> 00:16:48,820
So control is no longer a zero-sum game.

297
00:16:48,820 --> 00:16:50,820
You have this control. You have this control. And all you put together,

298
00:16:50,820 --> 00:16:54,820
in partnership, brings about the best music.

299
00:16:54,820 --> 00:16:56,820
So Kleiber is about process.

300
00:16:56,820 --> 00:16:58,820
Kleiber is about conditions in the world.

301
00:16:58,820 --> 00:17:02,820
But you need to have process and content to create the meaning.

